# Create a function to quickly create a kable with specific styling
get_kable <- function(df) {
  df %>%
    sample_n(5) %>%
    kable() %>%
    kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed", "responsive"))
}

# Create a function to simulate finding the mode of any attribute
Mode <- function(x) {
  ux <- unique(x)
  ux[which.max(tabulate(match(x, ux)))]
}

# Read in champion id data
champs <- read_csv("champs.csv") %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  select(champion = name, championid = id)

# Read in match data
matches <- read_csv("matches.csv") %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  select(matchid = id, seasonid, duration, version)

# Read in stats data in each data frame
stats1 <- read_csv("stats1.csv")
stats2 <- read_csv("stats2.csv")
# Add the two data frames together
stats <- rbind(stats1, stats2) %>%
  drop_na()

# Read in match participants data
participants <- read_csv("participants.csv") %>%
  drop_na()

# Read in match bans data
teambans <- read_csv("teambans.csv") %>%
  drop_na()

Data Wrangling

# Extrapolate exact position data from role
participants$position[participants$role == "DUO_SUPPORT"] <- "SUPPORT"
participants$position[participants$role == "DUO_CARRY"] <- "CARRY"
participants <- participants %>%
  # Filter out bot lane champs that didn't get assigned the right position
  filter(position != "BOT") %>%
  # Don't need the role since position was extrapolated
  select(-role) %>%
  # Classify participants into teams based off of player number
  mutate(team = ifelse(player <= 5, "BLUE", "RED"))

matches <- matches %>%
  # Get a more generalized version number using regex, ignore tiny patches
  extract(version, c("ver_major", "ver_minor"), "^([:digit:]+).([:digit:]+)") %>%
  type_convert(cols(ver_major = col_integer(), 
                    ver_minor = col_integer())) %>%
  mutate(ver = (ver_major * 100) + ver_minor) %>%
  # Ignore remakes (games less than 4 minutes, with 60 seconds of buffer in case)
  filter(duration > 300)

# Add the most common role to the participants data frame
participants <- participants %>%
  left_join(champs, by = "championid") %>%
  right_join(matches, by = "matchid")

# Create a new data frame with each champion's most common role in the most recent season
champ_roles <- participants %>%
  group_by(champion) %>% 
  summarize(common_role = Mode(position))

# Add primary champ roles to participants
participants <- participants %>%
  left_join(champ_roles, by = "champion")

# Refactor win from integer (1/0) to boolean (T/F)
stats <- stats %>%
  mutate(win = (win == 1))

teambans <- teambans %>%
  # Join the champion id's with names, only consider games where all bans are used
  left_join(champs, by = "championid") %>%
  # Add primary champ roles
  left_join(champ_roles, by="champion")

Game Duration

participants %>%
  group_by(ver_major, ver) %>%
  # Get the average duration for each version in seconds converted to minutes
  mutate(minutes = (duration / 60)) %>%
  summarize(avg_duration = mean(minutes)) %>%
  # Graph the resulting data with a line of best fit
  ggplot(aes(x = factor(ver), 
             y = avg_duration, 
             group = 1, 
             color=factor(ver_major))) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    geom_smooth(method = "loess") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
                                     vjust = 0.4, 
                                     size = 9)) +
    labs(x="Game Version",
         y="Average Duration (in minutes)",
         title="League of Legends Game Duration over Version") +
    scale_x_discrete(labels=ver_labels)

Flash key

participants %>%
  group_by(ver_major, ver) %>%
  # Only consider participants that actually take flash
  filter(ss1 == 4 | ss2 == 4) %>%
  # Get bool, TRUE if flash is on the D key
  mutate(flash = (ss1 == 4)) %>%
  # Get percentage with flash on D for each version
  summarize(avg_flash = 100 * mean(flash)) %>%
  # Graph the resulting data with a line of best fit

Winrate over KDA

# Create a new data frame to calculate kda
kda_stats <- stats

# Treat entities with 0 deaths as 1 for the purpose of KDA calculations
kda_stats$deaths[kda_stats$deaths == 0] <- 1

kda_stats %>%
  # Calculate kda for each entity
  mutate(kda = (kills + assists)/deaths) %>%
  # Join with other stats to remove incalculable values
  right_join(select(participants, id), by = "id") %>%
  # Divide kda range into 25 buckets, scaled to each have the same size, plus one bucket for NA
  mutate(kda_range = cut(kda, breaks=quantile(kda, probs=seq(0,1,len=26), na.rm=TRUE))) %>%
  # Get winrate for each KDA range
  group_by(kda_range) %>%
  summarize(winrate = 100 * mean(win)) %>%
  # Graph the resulting data for each KDA, with a line in between
  ggplot(aes(y = winrate, 
             x = kda_range, 
             color = kda_range, 
             group = 1)) +
    geom_point(na.rm=TRUE) +
    geom_line(na.rm=TRUE) +
    labs(x="KDA Range",
         y="Average Winrate",
         title="Winrate by Kills and Assists per Death (KDA)") +
    guides(color=FALSE) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
                                     vjust = 0.4))

CS/Min

Calculate CS/Min for each person in each game

cs_df <- stats %>%
  # CS = creep score = minions killed
  select(id, win, cs = totminionskilled) %>%
  # Join with participant data to get position
  right_join(participants, by = "id") %>%
  # Only include positions that kill the CS in a lane
  filter(position == "CARRY" | position == "MID" | position == "TOP") %>%
  # Divide CS  by duration to get CS/min rate
  mutate(cs_min = cs/(duration/60)) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  select(win, cs_min, champion, matchid, team)

Calculate team average CS/Min for each game

team_cs_df <- cs_df %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  # Get average CS/Min for each champion
  group_by(champion) %>%
  mutate(avg_cs = mean(cs_min)) %>%
  # Get average CS/Min for each team and whether they won
  group_by(matchid, team) %>%
  summarize(win = max(win), team_cs = mean(avg_cs)) %>%
  # Get the average CS/Min of each team's opponent
  group_by(matchid) %>%
  mutate(cs_lag = lag(team_cs), 
         cs_lead = lead(team_cs))

# Combine the CS/Min opponent columsn into one column
team_cs_df$enemy_cs <- team_cs_df$cs_lag
team_cs_df$enemy_cs[!is.na(team_cs_df$cs_lead)] = team_cs_df$cs_lead[!is.na(team_cs_df$cs_lead)]

team_cs_df <- team_cs_df %>%
  select(-cs_lag, -cs_lead) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  # Calculate the CS/Min difference between each team and their opponent
  mutate(cs_diff = team_cs - enemy_cs)

Winrate

Calculate overall and side-biased winrates for each champion

winrate_df <- participants %>%
  select(id, team, champion) %>%
  # Get participant stats
  left_join(stats, by = "id") %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  # Refactor win from integer (1/0) to boolean (T/F)
  mutate(win = (win == 1)) %>%
  # Get average champ winrate overall
  group_by(champion) %>%
  mutate(champ_wr = mean(win)) %>%
  # Get winrate for each champion based on team side
  group_by(champion, team) %>%
  summarize(team_wr = mean(win), champ_wr = mean(champ_wr)) %>%
  ungroup()

Test correlation between two methods of team winrates and actual winrate

wr_df <- winrate_df %>%
  # Join winrate stats to player stats
  inner_join(participants, by = c("team", "champion")) %>% 
  inner_join(stats, by = "id") %>%
  # Calculate two average winrates for each team and whether that team won
  group_by(matchid, team) %>%
  summarize(win = mean(win), 
            # Winrate based off of overall champion winrate
            champ_wr = mean(champ_wr), 
            # Winrate based off of what team the champ is playing on
            team_wr = mean(team_wr)) %>%
  # Get the winrate stats for each team's opponent
  group_by(matchid) %>%
  mutate(team_lag = lag(team_wr), 
         team_lead = lead(team_wr), 
         champ_lag = lag(champ_wr), 
         champ_lead = lead(champ_wr))

# Combine regular enemy winrate into one column
wr_df$enemy_wr <- wr_df$team_lag
wr_df$enemy_wr[!is.na(wr_df$team_lead)] = wr_df$team_lead[!is.na(wr_df$team_lead)]

# Combine scaled enemy winrate into one column
wr_df$enemy_cwr <- wr_df$champ_lag
wr_df$enemy_cwr[!is.na(wr_df$champ_lead)] = wr_df$champ_lead[!is.na(wr_df$champ_lead)]

wr_df <- wr_df %>% 
  # Calculate winrate differences between each team and their opponent
  mutate(t_wr_diff = team_wr - enemy_wr, 
         c_wr_diff = champ_wr - enemy_cwr) %>%
  select(win, c_wr_diff, t_wr_diff) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  ungroup()
## Adding missing grouping variables: `matchid`
wr_df %>%
  # Data is reflected around 0, so only get half the data
  filter(t_wr_diff >= 0 | c_wr_diff >= 0) %>%
  # Cut each winrate range with the same distances
  mutate(t_range = cut(t_wr_diff, breaks=quantile(t_wr_diff, probs=seq(0,1,len=21)))) %>%
  mutate(c_range = cut(c_wr_diff, breaks=quantile(t_wr_diff, probs=seq(0,1,len=21)))) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  # Get the winrate for each team-based winrate range
  group_by(t_range) %>%
  mutate(t_wr = mean(win)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  # Get the winrate for each overall winrate range
  group_by(c_range) %>%
  mutate(c_wr = mean(win)) %>%
  # Graph each winrate range to compare which one has better correlation
  ggplot(aes(group = 1)) +
    geom_point(aes(x = t_range, y = t_wr, color = "Scaled for side")) +
    geom_point(aes(x = c_range, y = c_wr, color = "Unscaled")) +
    geom_line(aes(x = t_range, y = t_wr, color = "Scaled for side")) +
    geom_line(aes(x = c_range, y = c_wr, color = "Unscaled")) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
    labs(x="Winrate Difference Range",
         y="Average Winrate",
         title="Team Winrate over Champ Winrate Comparing Scaled vs Unscaled",
         color="Winrate Method")

Damage ratios

Calculate average damage ratios for all champions

avg_dmg <- participants %>%
  select(id, player, champion, common_role) %>%
  left_join(stats, by = "id") %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  # Get average damage dealt in each category for each champion
  group_by(champion) %>%
  summarize(avg_magic_dealt = mean(magicdmgtochamp),
         avg_phys_dealt = mean(physdmgtochamp),
         avg_true_dealt = mean(truedmgtochamp)) %>%
  # Get damage ratios for each champion
  mutate(physmagic_dealt_ratio = avg_phys_dealt / avg_magic_dealt,
         true_dealt_ratio = avg_true_dealt / (avg_phys_dealt + avg_magic_dealt)) %>%
  select(champion, physmagic_dealt_ratio, true_dealt_ratio)

Visualize damage ratio over winrate and find optimal ratio

ratio_df <- participants %>%
  # Join with stats to get win
  inner_join(stats, by = "id") %>%
  # Join to get each champion's average damage
  left_join(avg_dmg, by = "champion") %>%
  # Get each team's average physical to magic damage ratio and whether they won
  group_by(matchid, team) %>%
  summarize(physmagic_ratio = mean(physmagic_dealt_ratio), win = max(win)) %>%
  ungroup()
## Warning: Column `champion` joining character vector and factor, coercing
## into character vector
ratio_df %>%
  # Divide the ratio into 50 evenly sized ranges
  mutate(ratio_range = cut(physmagic_ratio, breaks=quantile(physmagic_ratio, probs=seq(0,1,len=50)))) %>%
  # Get the winrate for each range
  group_by(ratio_range) %>%
  summarize(wr = mean(win)) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  # Graph the winrate of each range to find optimal ratio
  ggplot(aes(x = ratio_range, 
             y = wr, 
             group = 1)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    geom_smooth(method = 'loess') +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, 
                                     vjust = 0.5,
                                     hjust = 1)) +
      labs(x = "Physical to Magic Damage Ratio Range",
           y = "Average Winrate",
           title = "Winrate over Damage Ratio")

Role Banned

Calculate roles banned for each team

avg_bans <- teambans %>%
  # Tidy bans giving each their own column
  mutate(is_top = (common_role=="TOP")) %>%
  mutate(is_jungle = (common_role=="JUNGLE")) %>%
  mutate(is_mid = (common_role=="MID")) %>%
  mutate(is_carry = (common_role=="CARRY")) %>%
  mutate(is_support = (common_role=="SUPPORT")) %>%
  # Get percentage of bans used on each role for each match
  group_by(matchid) %>%
  summarize(pct_top = mean(is_top),
            pct_jungle = mean(is_jungle),
            pct_mid = mean(is_mid),
            pct_carry = mean(is_carry),
            pct_support = mean(is_support))

# Store aesthetic variables for each of the positions
top_aes <- aes(y = ban_top, color = "Top")
jungle_aes <- aes(y = ban_jungle, color = "Jungle")
mid_aes <- aes(y = ban_mid, color = "Mid")
carry_aes <- aes(y = ban_carry, color = "Carry")
support_aes <- aes(y = ban_support, color = "Support")

# Quick functions to get specific plot settings
Smooth <- function(ae) {
  geom_smooth(ae, method='loess', size = 2)
}
Point <- function(ae) {
  geom_point(ae, alpha = 0.2)
}
Line <- function(ae) {
  geom_line(ae, alpha = 0.3)
}

matches %>%
  inner_join(avg_bans, by="matchid") %>%
  # Get average bans used on each role for each version
  group_by(ver) %>%
  summarize(ban_top = mean(pct_top),
            ban_jungle = mean(pct_jungle),
            ban_mid = mean(pct_mid),
            ban_carry = mean(pct_carry),
            ban_support = mean(pct_support)) %>%
  # Graph bans on each role by version
  ggplot(aes(factor(ver), 
             group = 1)) +
    # Add points for each role
    Point(top_aes) + Point(jungle_aes) + Point(mid_aes) + Point(carry_aes) + Point(support_aes) +
    # Add a line between points
    Line(top_aes) + Line(jungle_aes) + Line(mid_aes) + Line(carry_aes) + Line(support_aes) +
    # Add a line of best fit for each role
    Smooth(top_aes) + Smooth(jungle_aes) + Smooth(mid_aes) + Smooth(carry_aes) + Smooth(support_aes) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,
                                     vjust = 0.4,
                                     size=10)) +
    labs(x = "Game Version Number",
         y = "Percentage of Bans Used",
         title = "Percentages of Bans Used on Each Role over Version") +
    scale_x_discrete(labels=ver_labels)
